The area under the receiver operating characteristic (ROC) curve is often
 used as a single summary measure.
 A larger AUC is better.
 A perfect forecast has AUC=1.
 Though the minimum value is 0, an AUC of 0.5 indicates no skill.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\series medium
The area under the curve can be estimated in a variety of ways.
 In MET, the simplest trapezoid method is used to calculate the area.
 AUC is calculated from the series of hit rate (POD) and false alarm rate
 (POFD) values (see the ROC entry below) for each user-specified threshold.
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout

$$
\backslash
hbox{AUC}=
\backslash
frac{1}{2}
\backslash
sum_{i=1}^{Nthresh}(POD_{i+1}+POD_i)(POFD_{i+1}-POFD_i)$$
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

